      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fc9b743e-20a1-4932-81b3-004a10011ede",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa-solid fa-desktop\"></i> Transition: Have students spend the remainder of the class time using what they’ve learned to create their own music. The instructions include some suggestions for what their project should include."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fc9b743e-20a1-4932-81b3-004a10011ede",
        "lesson_activity.key": "eb3dbace-f6fe-46cd-8e5a-0901a1957364"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2cd93f46-82cb-4a99-a539-55eb1dfd69f9",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-check\"></i> Do This:** Review the objectives of the lesson. Have students show a thumbs up/down/sideways to reflect on whether they reached each objective. \n\n**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-check\"></i> Do This:** Have students set up for a quick Turn & Talk to reexamine the Question of the Day. Some supportive leading questions might be: Why do we use functions instead of rewwriting out every single line of code? If you were a computer could you read a short paragraph or a long story quicker? What if we want to make a change to the code? \n\n**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-microphone\"></i> Say:** Take turns listening and answering the Question of the Day. Give me a thumbs up after you both have shared your answers.  \n\n**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-check\"></i> Do This:** This is an optional activity to encourage your students to share the creative music they’ve built with code. Consider adding an opportunity for students to share ‘glows and grows’ after they share their projects with each other. \n"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2cd93f46-82cb-4a99-a539-55eb1dfd69f9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "bf029be1-faa4-4a35-bd77-b0c12af7fc32"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b9ea5ada-cb79-46ff-92cf-2e05ee11dd97",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-comments\"></i> Discuss:** How can we make our programs more interactive and expressive?\n\n**<i class=\"fa-duotone fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> Discussion Goal:** Get students thinking about how they can make their programs more fun and creative by adding ways for people to interact with them. Help them imagine how cool it would be if their music changed when someone pressed a key or clicked a button, setting the stage for adding interactivity to their projects.",
        "name": "Lesson Set Up"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b9ea5ada-cb79-46ff-92cf-2e05ee11dd97",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a0111bad-4a0f-428b-9b88-50570e07a43f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "94cc296b-6c01-456e-b2a6-6656743782e8",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-check\"></i> Do This:** Set students up to play Simon Says [Sounds Edition] using the instructions and example commands on the slide. Rotate the leader, Simon, for as long as time allows. \n\n**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-microphone\"></i> Say:** This game works similarly to events in computer programming. We were always waiting for the “trigger (Simon Says)” to signify we should do an action. If the trigger wasn’t there, we didn’t do anything. \n\n**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-check\"></i> Do This:** Finish the warm up activity with an explanation of how events can be used to make code more interactive and respond to user inputs. They will be practicing customizing and creating events in code in the next activity in Music Lab. \n",
        "name": "Warm Up Activity"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "94cc296b-6c01-456e-b2a6-6656743782e8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a0111bad-4a0f-428b-9b88-50570e07a43f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "25c7741d-9c12-447a-84f9-b8fb2ff3a8c9",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Intro Video"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "25c7741d-9c12-447a-84f9-b8fb2ff3a8c9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e1fc288f-d1f3-4c80-8fce-5dadd77adbc7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b1b175df-1a47-47a3-a005-2e2a36bdad9b",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-check\"></i> Do This:** Watch the video on level 1 together as a class. \n\n**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-comments\"></i> Discuss:** Discuss other creative jobs that connect music and technology\n\n**<i class=\"fa-duotone fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> Discussion Goal:** Students might think of how a sound designer uses technology to create sound effects for movies and video games. They use special software to mix sounds and make everything sound realistic. Another example is a music producer, who uses digital tools to edit and improve songs before they are released.\n"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b1b175df-1a47-47a3-a005-2e2a36bdad9b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e1fc288f-d1f3-4c80-8fce-5dadd77adbc7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2154567b-18d8-407a-8257-8ec95edf0c15",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2154567b-18d8-407a-8257-8ec95edf0c15",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e1fc288f-d1f3-4c80-8fce-5dadd77adbc7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d0f68306-857d-439c-8f3c-4b4ed49836e6",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-check\"></i> Do This:** Read the instructions for level 2 together as a class. Important tips to point out:\nGuide students to notice the green event triggers. \nEvents stand alone and do not connecto the main program. \nThe sounds connected to events only play when the button (on the keyboard or on screen left of Run) is pressed. \nMake a connection to the Simon Says activity in the warm up and encourage students to consider the use of a event to make the program interactive and fun.\n\n**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-desktop\"></i> Transition:** Have students transition to continuing the lesson on their own devices. They will work on levels 3-10 independently. \n\n\n\n\n"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d0f68306-857d-439c-8f3c-4b4ed49836e6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e1fc288f-d1f3-4c80-8fce-5dadd77adbc7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d6a8aaea-c7a2-45db-a951-80dc471387a0",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Skill Building"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d6a8aaea-c7a2-45db-a951-80dc471387a0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e1fc288f-d1f3-4c80-8fce-5dadd77adbc7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d42f0f9d-a40d-4332-b4bb-aacf814510ea",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-microphone\"></i> Say:** Read the instructions for each level and try to complete the code. Press the Run button to try it out. If something is not quite right you will get a hint under the instructions. When you’ve successfully completed the challenge, a new message and a Continue button will appear. Click Continue to move to the next level and move at your speed. \n\n**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-retweet\"></i> Circulate:** Encourage students to read the instructions and hints on each level as you circulate. Ask guiding questions to support students if they get stuck. \n\n**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-check\"></i> Do This:** Level 8 is an opportunity to check for understanding in the class. \n\n"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d42f0f9d-a40d-4332-b4bb-aacf814510ea",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e1fc288f-d1f3-4c80-8fce-5dadd77adbc7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0353181f-6c32-40a0-95dc-930ee1578205",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Freeplay"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0353181f-6c32-40a0-95dc-930ee1578205",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e1fc288f-d1f3-4c80-8fce-5dadd77adbc7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1e206d9c-d63e-418d-a857-46d9d7016ee1",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-desktop\"></i> Transition:** Have students spend the remainder of the class time using what they’ve learned to create their own music. The instructions include some suggestions for what their project should include.\n"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1e206d9c-d63e-418d-a857-46d9d7016ee1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e1fc288f-d1f3-4c80-8fce-5dadd77adbc7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2cd7b449-5201-4406-ba43-a96580ce0edd",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-check\"></i> Do This:** Review the objectives of the lesson. Have students show a thumbs up/down/sideways to reflect on whether they reached each objective. \n\n**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-check\"></i> Do This:** Review the question of the day.\n\n**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-comments\"></i> Discuss:** How did we make our programs more interactive and expressive?\n\n**<i class=\"fa-duotone fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> Discussion Goal:** Encourage students to reflect on how they made their programs more fun and creative by adding ways for people to interact with them. Have them share examples of the sounds and events they used and why.\n\n**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-check\"></i> Do This:** Give students time to write their reflections on paper or any avenue you prefer. If time allows have them share at least one reflection with a partner and and then submit the reflection to you. \n\n**<i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-check\"></i> Optional Do This:** This is an optional activity to encourage your students to share the creative music they’ve built with code. Consider adding an opportunity for students to share ‘glows and grows’ after they share their projects with each other. \n\n"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2cd7b449-5201-4406-ba43-a96580ce0edd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7ad3be3a-fdb0-4240-be54-378acb6705ce"
      }
    }
  ],
